- "hidden treasures of cinema" refers to specific videos;
- "pearls of language" represent unique and valuable languages in which the videos are provided;
- "captains of direction" symbolizes the directors of the videos;
- "depths of viewer engagement surpass the threshold of prolonged interest" means the average watch time exceeds 120 minutes;
- "golden sands of feedback" indicate the ratings and sentiments from viewers.

- "gardeners" refers to users;
- "flowers" are videos;
- "warmth of their care" is the rating given by the user;
- "tender whispers" are the comments provided by the user;
- "moods of their hearts" represent the sentiment of the feedback;
- "depth of their roots" indicates the engagement level;
- "garden of feedback" signifies the feedback table;
- "feelings of neutrality and positivity" correspond to sentiment values 'neutral' and 'positive'.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(user_id) AS beginner_count
FROM user_engagement_levels
WHERE engagement_level = 'beginner';

SELECT engagement_level, last_update_date
FROM user_engagement_levels
WHERE engagement_level IN ('beginner', 'intermediate');
